<section id="fs-id1170571042944" class="key-concepts">
<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list id="fs-id1170571042951" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet">
<item>A direction field is a mathematical object used to graphically represent solutions to a first-order differential equation.</item>
<item>Euler’s Method is a numerical technique that can be used to approximate solutions to a differential equation.</item>
</list>
</section>
<section id="fs-id1170571042967" class="key-equations">
<title>Key Equations</title>
<table id="eip-516" summary="." class="unnumbered unstyled">
<tgroup cols="2"><tbody>
  <row>
    <entry><emphasis effect="bold">Euler’s Method</emphasis></entry>
    <entry><m:math><m:mtable><m:mtr><m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:msub><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mi>h</m:mi></m:mtd></m:mtr><m:mtr><m:mtd columnalign="left"><m:msub><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mi>n</m:mi></m:msub><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mtext>where</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mi>h</m:mi><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>is the step size</m:mtext></m:mtd></m:mtr></m:mtable></m:math></entry>
